RISK
Some team members might fail to contribute as expected, or behave in other ways detrimental to the project.


What methods of communication seem to work best when teams want to let their team member(s) know that their behaviour is hurting the team?


What kind of teammate contribution reports are the most effective in reducing this risk?


What kind of tools have you seen successfully automate tracking teammate contribution?
